    text: `Website chat is part of phone answering at £${pricing.tiers.core.price}/month. Unlimited chimney conversations — from pot replacement enquiries to multi-chimney breast removal projects.`
  }
];

const faqs = [
  {
    question: "How do I install chat on my chimney website?",
    answer: "You do not need to — we do it for you. During onboarding, our team adds the chat widget to your website regardless of the platform you use. WordPress, Wix, a basic HTML site built by a mate — it all works. If you prefer to keep control or have a web developer who manages your site, we will provide the code snippet and they can drop it in within a couple of minutes. Most chimney specialists just let us handle it and get back to repointing stacks."
  },
  {
    question: "Can the AI advise on chimney damp causes?",
    answer: "Your company profile configures the AI with your diagnostic approach. When a visitor types 'we have a brown stain spreading on the chimney wall — what causes this?' the AI responds from your profile context — mentioning common causes like failed pointing, cracked liners, and cement capping that traps moisture — while capturing the staining colour, the building age, and whether the flue is active or disused."
  },
  {
    question: "What does chat capture from chimney visitors?",
    answer: "The AI gathers the chimney problem type (damp, structural, lining, or removal), the staining description if applicable, the chimney position (ridge, gable, or party wall), the building age and type, whether the flue is active, any previous repair attempts, and the visitor's contact information for your follow-up."
  },
  {
    question: "Does chat slow my chimney website?",
    answer: "Your chimney project galleries, case study photographs, and accreditation badge graphics load at their normal speed. The chat interface initialises only after all existing page content has rendered. No performance impact on any device or connection."
  },
  {
    question: "Is website chat a separate charge?",
    answer: `Website chat comes included with phone answering in the Core plan at £${pricing.tiers.core.price}/month. For chimney specialists, both channels serve distinct enquiry patterns: daytime phone calls from stove installers booking lining jobs and developers ordering breast removals, and evening website conversations from homeowners diagnosing chimney damp while rain drives water through their failed pointing.`
  },
  {
    question: "How is visitor data from chimney queries handled?",
    answer: "Chat conversations containing property addresses, chimney fault descriptions, structural details about breast removal, flue conditions, and visitor contact information are encrypted and stored on UK and EU servers under UK GDPR. Lead summaries go exclusively to you. No chimney project details reach competitors or third parties."
  }
];
