<ChannelTradeLayout
  title="AI Website Chat for UK Chimney Specialists | Rapid Receptionist"
  description={`AI website chat for UK chimney specialists. Engages homeowners researching chimney damp and stove installers planning flue liners. Included at £${pricing.tiers.core.price}/month.`}
  canonicalUrl="/chimney-specialists/ai-website-chat/"
  channelName="AI Website Chat"
  tradeName="Chimney Specialist"
  tradeNamePlural="Chimney Specialists"
  tradeSlug="chimney-specialists"
  headline="AI Website Chat for UK Chimney Specialist Companies"
  accentWord="Chimney"
  subhead="A homeowner finds your site at 10pm after noticing their chimney stack leaning visibly in strong wind. They describe cracked render, loose pots, and missing mortar. Chat captures the lead overnight."
  scenario="It is 11pm on a Thursday. A stove installer types: 'Hi — I install wood burning stoves and need a chimney specialist to line a flue for me. The property is a thatched cottage near Woodstock, seventeenth-century. The existing flue is an old rubble construction — no liner of any kind. The building is Grade II listed. I am fitting a Clearview Pioneer 400 inset stove. I need a 904 grade liner because the appliance burns wood only, the flue is about 9 metres, and the listing means any external work must be invisible from the ground. Conservation officer requires lime mortar for any repointing. Can you do 904 liners in listed buildings? Need this done week after next.' Without chat, he emails Friday. With AI Website Chat, the AI confirms that 904 stainless is correct for wood-only appliances, asks about the flue route (straight or offset), and captures: thatched cottage Woodstock, 17th century, Grade II, rubble flue, no existing liner, 904 grade, 9m, Clearview Pioneer 400, conservation officer requirement, lime mortar, invisible from ground, week after next."
  benefits={benefits}
  faqs={faqs}
  channelPageUrl="/construction-trades/ai-website-chat/"
  tradePageUrl="/chimney-specialists/ai-receptionist/"
  ctaHeadline="Win the Iffley Chimney Investigation While She Listens to Dripping at 9:15pm"
  ctaSubhead={`A homeowner hears water dripping behind her sealed fireplace while brown staining spreads above. Chat captures the 1890s terrace, concrete slab cap, and missing ventilation. Included at £${pricing.tiers.core.price}/month.`}
/>
